Sentencas: Ni-P amorphous alloy coatings with different P content are coated onto porous Ni foam by means of electroless plating.
Titulo: Ni-P coated Ni foam as coking resistant current collector for solid oxide fuel cells fed by syngas

Sentencas: The plated Ni foams exhibit excellent carbon deposition resistance and structure stability in syngas at elevated temperature when P content is higher than 6.5 wt% in the coating.
Titulo: Ni-P coated Ni foam as coking resistant current collector for solid oxide fuel cells fed by syngas

Sentencas: Anode supported solid oxide fuel cells fabricated using a spin coating process have a maximum power density of similar to 1.3 W cm(-2) in H-2 at 850 degrees C and similar to 0.8 W cm(-2) in syngas at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Ni-P coated Ni foam as coking resistant current collector for solid oxide fuel cells fed by syngas

Sentencas: The H-2-fueled cells with naked and plated Ni foam current collector have very similar internal ohmic resistance and power density, which confirm the good electronic conductivity of the coatings.
Titulo: Ni-P coated Ni foam as coking resistant current collector for solid oxide fuel cells fed by syngas

Sentencas: The syngas-fueled cells with Au mesh and plated Ni foam current collector reach almost identical power density and internal resistance, and the latter has no apparent degradation of power output during extended fuel cell stability testing.
Titulo: Ni-P coated Ni foam as coking resistant current collector for solid oxide fuel cells fed by syngas

Sentencas: Thus Ni-P is a promising carbon deposition resistant coating of current collector for syngas-fueled solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Ni-P coated Ni foam as coking resistant current collector for solid oxide fuel cells fed by syngas
